# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BillShield Server — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to server/.env and fill in real values.
# server/.env is gitignored — NEVER commit real keys.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Override the default listen port (default: 3001).
# PORT=3001


# ── Model Routing Tier 1: Strong paid models (high-risk extraction tasks) ─────
# Used as PRIMARY for: docTypeAgent, billExtractionAgent, eobExtractionAgent, comparisonAgent
# Fallback order within this tier: Anthropic → OpenAI

# Anthropic (PRIMARY for high-risk extraction and final fallback for summary/action)
# Without this, extraction falls back to OpenAI (if set), then deterministic-only output.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# OpenAI (FALLBACK for high-risk extraction)
# Without this, only Anthropic is used for extraction with no vendor fallback.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...


# ── Model Routing Tier 2: Cheap / free models (low-risk generation tasks) ────
# Used as PRIMARY for: summaryAgent, actionAgent
# Fallback order: MiroFish → Gemini Flash → Anthropic (tier 1 as final paid fallback)

# MiroFish (PRIMARY cheap provider for summary and action wording)
# Requires all three vars. If any is missing, MiroFish is skipped and Gemini is tried next.
# MIROFISH_API_KEY=mf-...
# MIROFISH_BASE_URL=https://api.mirofish.ai/v1
# MIROFISH_MODEL=mirofish-default

# Google Gemini Flash (mid-tier cheap, used between MiroFish and Anthropic)
# Very low cost. Without this, summary/action fall directly to Anthropic as paid fallback.
# GEMINI_API_KEY=AIza...


# ── Minimum viable configuration ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY alone enables: extraction, classification, summary, action.
#
# Without ANY keys, the pipeline still runs in deterministic-only mode:
#   - classification: regex marker scoring
#   - extraction:     regex amounts/dates (confidence ~0.2)
#   - summary:        safe template (numbers from extraction, generic wording)
#   - action:         safe template (one call script or email draft)
#   - flags:          deterministic rules only (minimum 3 guaranteed)
#   - needs_human_review: true (weak scores trigger this automatically)
